$interpreted: Tica: Hoho~ this is quite amazing. I absolutely made the right decision by putting the headmaster's mission on hold first!
Tica: This singing...must be what the two soldiers mentioned. It's coming from that direction!
Tica: The singing disappeared again...
Tica: Hmm? Could it be that it's coming from inside here?
Tica: Atlas Marionette Workshop I...better check out what's inside.
Tica: Eww~ Why are there so many marionettes. It's kinda creepy and gross...
Tica: Who's there!?
Tica: That's strange...am I just seeing things?
Tica: ...Hmm, something's on the table.

Tica: ...In Atlas, when a resident passes away, 
family members will craft a marionette for the deceased relative.
Tica: They will then keep it in their home as a memento. The people of Atlas believe that the soul of their relative will be attached to the marionette.
Tica: These are the traditions of the marionette religion that have been passed down for hundreds of years...
Tica: I see; no wonder there are so many marionettes here. As long as I know the reasoning, you guys won't scare me one bit.
Tica: Woah! EXCEPT when you're moving around that! That's SUPER freaky!
Tica: But how did they...is it because of the singing?
Tica: Hey, whaddya want? If you want to pick a fight, I won't back down from your offer!
Tica: Whew~ Finally dealt with all of them.
Tica: Hmmm, these marionettes are different from the others. Only these have runes carved into them, and they glow black for some reason.
Tica: Just what the heck is going on?
Tica: Looks like something bizarre is indeed going down here...
Tica: Hehe, this is getting more and more fun by the minute. Freaky mystery, you're going down!
